    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{12x-60}{-70-49x-7x^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{4x^{2}-20x}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}{7x\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}, x\ne 5\hbox{ and }x\ne -2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{12x-60}{-70-49x-7x^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{4x^{2}-20x}} 
      \amp = \frac{{12x-60}}{-7x^2-49x - 70} \cdot {\frac{x^{2}+4x+4}{4x^{2}-20x}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{12\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)}}{{-7\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+7x+10\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(x+2\right)^{2}}}{{4x\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{12\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)}}{{-7\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(x+2\right)^{2}}}{{4x\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)}{7x\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}, x\ne 5\hbox{ and }x\ne -2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>x-5</m> and <m>x + 2</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {5, -2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
